    Courses        Courses  Fall 2020 Honors Courses  Honors Courses Listing  All Honors College students MUST register for either HON 222 or HON 322 each semester**  If you are a freshman, sophomore or junior, register for HON 222.       HON 222   HON 222 – Honors Activity  0 credit hours, required each term, except for summer, for all Honors College students. Satisfactory/Unsatisfactory grade.  Call numbers:   42829 (for first year students only)  13772 (for students whose last name starts with A through K)  13773 (for students whose last name starts with L through Z)  38177 (for students studying abroad; departmental approval required)   If you are a senior, and you intend to conduct work this term to satisfy your Honors capstone, register for HON 322.       HON 322   HON 322 – Honors Capstone Activity  0 credit hours. Satisfactory/Unsatisfactory grade  Call number:   29074: HON 322 – Honors Capstone   The UIC Undergraduate Catalog will no longer be available to anyone in a printed form. The catalog is available to view online.       Spring 2020 Course Syllabi     HON 101: First Year Orientation Seminar         HON 101    HON 101 | All sections         HON Gen. Ed. Core Courses (100 Level)         Core Courses    HON 120 | CRN: 26283 | Human Rights and International Relations | Instructor: A. Feldmann  HON 121 | CRN: 42078 | Fiction & Non-Fiction of the Anthropocene | Instructor: V. Audiutori  HON 121 | CRN: 26285 | Poetics of Dissent | Instructor: C. Glomski  HON 121 | CRN: 41762 | Utopias & Dystopias: Idyllic & Nightmarish Worlds | Instructor: J. Lewis  HON 121 | CRN: 38662 | Social & Historical Concepts of Design: Art, Film & Dreams | Instructor: S. Malagrino  HON 121 | CRN: 26284 | Decentering Whiteness in Bioethics | Instructor: E. Rabelais  HON 121 | CRN: 41763 | Superheroes & Cultural Mythology | Instructor: B. Superfine  HON 122 | CRN: 40597 | Comparing Cities: Urban Trajectories, Problems and Solutions in the Archaeological Past and Recent Times | Instru